            <div class="common-banner col-top-banner" data-config="{'backgroundColor':'#e3f4ff', 'backgroundImage':'//wacnppe.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/marketing-resource/media/images/production/container-registry_banner.png','imageHeight':'auto'}">
                <div class="common-banner-image">
                    <div class="common-banner-title">
                        <img src="//wacnppe.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/marketing-resource/media/images/production/container-registry.svg" alt=""/>
                        <h2>Container Registry <span style="color: #4d4d4d;font-family: '微软雅黑',regular;font-size: 20px;top: -6px;position: relative;display: inline;">(Preview) </span><span>Container Registry</span></h2>
                        <h4>Store and manage container images across all Azure deployment types</h4>
                        <em><a href="/pricing/1rmb-trial/" id="container-registry_1rmb-trial">1RMB Trial<i class="icon icon-arrow-right-thin"></i></a></em> <a href="/pricing/pia/" id="container-registry_pia">Buy Now<i class="icon icon-arrow-right-thin"></i></a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- END: container-registry-TopBanner --> <!-- BEGIN: container-registry-Content -->
            <div class="pricing-page-section">
                <div class="cognitive-figure">
                    <div class="col-md-3">
                        <img src="//wacnppe.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/marketing-resource/media/images/service/container-registry-01-manage-containers.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <h2>Manage images for all types of containers</h2>
                        <p>Azure Container Registry allows to store images for all types of container deployments including DC/OS, Docker Swarm, Kubernetes, and Azure services such as App Service, Batch, Service Fabric, and others. The DevOps team can manage the configuration of apps isolated from the configuration of the hosting environment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="cognitive-figure">
                    <div class="col-md-3">
                        <img src="//wacnppe.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/marketing-resource/media/images/service/container-registry-03-keep-containers.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <h2>Keep container images close</h2>
                        <p>Reduce network latency and eliminate ingress/egress charges by keeping the Docker Registry in the same data center as the deployments. Azure Container Registry provides a local close-range storage of the container images within the subscription, and full control over access and image names.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="cognitive-figure">
                    <div class="col-md-3">
                        <img src="//wacnppe.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/marketing-resource/media/images/service/container-registry-04-docker-cli.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <h2>Uses the familiar open-source Docker CLI tools</h2>
                        <p>There is no need to learn the new APIs or commands. Because Azure Container Registry is compatible with the open-source Docker Registry v2, it is able to use the same open-source Docker CLI tools that users are familiar with and the known skills to efficiently interact with the registry.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
				
                <div class="cognitive-figure">
                    <div class="col-md-3">
                        <img src="//wacnppe.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/marketing-resource/media/images/service/container-registry-05-expand-registry-funcionality.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <h2>Expand registry functionality</h2>
                        <p>Keep the images safe by authenticating and managing access with Azure Active Directory. Trigger events based on container actions with Webhooks. Both technologies are compatible with standard registries.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>			
            </div>
